Homework 1

Question 1:
syscal.c
The program demonstrates the operations of system calls from question 1
compile using:
gcc -o syscal syscal.c

Run using:
./syscal

Question 3:
copy.c
The Program will copy file a to file B using standard I/O read()/wirte() at a specified chunk and record the time it takes to transfer, the default is byte-by-byte transfer
Compile using:
gcc -o copy copy.c
For 3a run using:
./copy
For 3b run using:
./copy <transfer_chunk_size>

Generating File A at different sizes:
genfileA.c
genfileA.c generates a file A of a specified size
compile using:
gcc -o gen genfileA.c
run using:
./gen <file_size>


